<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Jithin Jith (Posts about osx)</title><link>https://j-jith.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://j-jith.github.io/categories/osx.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents Â© 2018 &lt;a href="mailto:"&gt;Jithin Jith&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 25 Jan 2018 03:53:52 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Letting Spotlight find Brew Apps on Mac OS X</title><link>https://j-jith.github.io/blog/letting-spotlight-find-brew-apps-on-mac-os-x/</link><dc:creator>Jithin Jith</dc:creator><description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Say, you want spotlight to find MacVim. Doing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_877435f0bd11429792e5826105bc8782-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;$ brew linkapps macvim
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;creates a symlink in &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;/Applications&lt;/tt&gt;. But Spotlight seems to ignore it. Instead, remove the symlink&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_78237d4808054299b3c081c7a82f1bbd-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;$ rm /Applications/MacVim.app
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;and do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a name="rest_code_17d418c872da454fbff8f035a407efd0-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;$ osascript -e &lt;span class="s1"&gt;'tell application "Finder" to make alias file to POSIX file "/usr/local/opt/macvim/MacVim.app" at POSIX file "/Applications"'&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>mac</category><category>osx</category><guid>https://j-jith.github.io/blog/letting-spotlight-find-brew-apps-on-mac-os-x/</guid><pubDate>Tue, 31 Oct 2017 05:22:05 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>